node.text:
_____________________________________

Things not seen from tonight’s episode.

(1) As I’ve gotten older my tolerance for BS has gone way down.

(2) It took 4 1/2 days of Hog Bear’s F-Ups before I finally snapped. Which I think is pretty good patience😉.

(3) The diesel specialist for this episode got Covid the day before. Luckily Turbo Tom got to Austin that day and I put him to work!

(4) It took 2 full days to tear down this Harvester. That’s the longest in Monster Garage History. Downside it left us with only 3 build days.

(5) The rear diff was scabbed from the front end of a MRAP and flipped so
It would work on the back of the Harvester.

(6) Hog Bear was only the second person I kicked off in the shows history.

(7) This was one of the physically toughest builds in the shows history. Especially with the fact that we were minus one builder for the entire week.

(8) Jesus I was a fat ass last year! Seeing myself this out of shape on TV is a great motivator to get healthy!

Let me know how you guys dig tonight’s episode..

#jessejames

node.text:
It’s time for us as Americans to stand the Fvck up and fight for our country. 

Fight for our fellow man. 

Fight for our freedoms that many have laid down their lives to preserve. 

United we Stand and Divided we Fall, should be ringing in everyone’s ears.

Just like this softball crowd. We need to take the lead and do what we are entitled to do.

Be Americans.

The only people that are going to
Save us, is Us.

🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸

@popeofwelding 
#jessejames

node.title: Now more than ever is not a time to stand on the sidelines..

node.text:
I try to do the hardest stuff possible. I mean stuff that kicks my ass physically and mentally. Stuff that takes years just to hone the skills and figure out the combination.
Stuff that at the end of the day I can barely stand up and my hands are bleeding and burned.
This way when all the copycats out there all of a sudden have these new ideas based those hard things I’m doing??

I’m like go right ahead and try!

I guess choosing the difficult path means built in job security..

#jessejames

node.text:
__________________________________

Spending the day today practicing this technique. It’s been 8 years since I did the first style keychains. 

They are for sure my favorite because they are made 100% by me in my shop.

Although it  does take a bit of practice to get the sequence down. Also using stainless this time so that means it needs to be hotter and I have to hit it harder.

The process goes like this.
-Material is cut to maximum length for my forge and heated to 2000°
-I hammer flats on the diamond with my Turkish power hammer.
-Then I stamp the logo on each flat.
-Then to the anvil to take the curve out of the material and hand hammer a flat in between each flat.
-Next to the Ironworker to pierce a hole between each flat centered on the flat spot I just hammered.
-finally they are parted off at a 45° angle so the end can be used as a bottle opener.
-Finally into the tumbler to knock the edges off and put a burnished finish on.

You really have to Focus and Boogie to get all these steps done in one heat!

It took me 4 or 5 bars to get my rhythm
Back down.

I used my @payupsucker stamp to practice, but I’m working on a new cool/funny stamp for the Contest keychains.

The contest officially Launches August 1st. But im going to keep the $25 pre-order deal going for a couple more days.

If you want one, or Five!

PayPal me $25 (friends/family)

—> Popeofwelding@jjfu.com 

Make sure you put Full Name and Shipping Address in the notes!

If you already ordered, Thank you! Better order a couple more for better odds!

Sweet!

@popeofwelding

node.text:
_____________________________________

Things not seen from tonight’s episode.

(1) As I’ve gotten older my tolerance for BS has gone way down.

(2) It took 4 1/2 days of Hog Bear’s F-Ups before I finally snapped. Which I think is pretty good patience😉.

(3) The diesel specialist for this episode got Covid the day before. Luckily Turbo Tom got to Austin that day and I put him to work!

(4) It took 2 full days to tear down this Harvester. That’s the longest in Monster Garage History. Downside it left us with only 3 build days.

(5) The rear diff was scabbed from the front end of a MRAP and flipped so
It would work on the back of the Harvester.

(6) Hog Bear was only the second person I kicked off in the shows history.

(7) This was one of the physically toughest builds in the shows history. Especially with the fact that we were minus one builder for the entire week.

(8) Jesus I was a fat ass last year! Seeing myself this out of shape on TV is a great motivator to get healthy!

Let me know how you guys dig tonight’s episode..

#jessejames

node.text:
Every once in a blue moon we sprinkle a little @westcoastchoppers Sugar on a Stock @harleydavidson 

When we do? 
They always come out over the top! Like this brand New Harley FatBoy. We touched every single part on the whole bike. Moved stuff around to make lots of subtle changes to improve the lines and the overall flow of the bike.
Also incorporated our New adjustable foot boards and pegs. And threw on a New Jesse James Titanium Exhaust from @redthunder_exhaust_official.

I say it looks pretty good!

Who has a keen eye and can spot all the changes??

(Sorry this bike is sold)

#jessejames 

www.WestCoastChoppers.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jesse James in Route 12 Filling Station with @terajoywight, @thebigrigbarbie, @munglesgarage, and @lonelystarroundup. May be an image of 3 people and people standing.

node.text:
Hey Hey

What a Day!

Thank you so much for everyone that made it out to the very first @lonelystarroundup 

I can’t tell you how humbled I am that with just 8 days notice. 500+ custom cars, trucks, exotics and bikes would show up and have a blast with me and my friends.

The biggest comments were how much fun people had. And so many kids getting to see some of this cool stuff for the first time.
That’s what it’s really all about.

Also thanks to my Amazing crew at @westcoastchoppers @jessejamesfirearms 
They busted major ass to pull this deal off in 8 days!!! Posters, Stickers, IG account, trophys!!
Shit we has a plane flying over with a JJFU banner!! Epic!

Also all my friends and partners that brought cars, bikes, fire trucks, displays, food, and beer. And the all Vet color guard. 
All of You did it with no guarantees and just off my word that it would be cool. 
For this you will be a part of this show for years to come.

And yes we will be doing the @lonelystarroundup Next year!!

Thank you Thank you 🙏🏻 

#jessejames
@popeofwelding
